# Commit Message Guidelines

Source: `assets/docs/guides/GIT_COMMITS_GUIDE.md` (primary), `assets/docs/guides/GIT_GUIDE.md` (extended)

## Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <description>

<body>
```

## Types

`feat` `fix` `docs` `style` `ref` `test` `chore` `ci` `build`

## Subject Line Rules

1. **≤50 characters**
2. Imperative mood — "Add feature" not "Added" or "Adds"
3. Capitalize first letter, no period
4. Blank line between subject and body
5. Wrap body at 72 characters

## Body

- Explain **WHAT and WHY**, not HOW
- Changes section: focus on intent, not implementation details

## Atomic Commits

One logical change per commit. Split if needed.
